# Cursor Rules for InsightVault Project

## Environment Configuration
- This is a Windows development environment
- Use PowerShell syntax, not bash syntax
- Use `;` for command chaining instead of `&&`
- Use `dir` instead of `ls` for listing files
- Use Windows path separators (`\`)

## Command Examples
- ✅ `cd backend; python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload`
- ❌ `cd backend && python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload`

## Project Structure
- Backend: Python/FastAPI in `backend/` directory
- Frontend: Next.js in `frontend/` directory
- Database: SQLite with Alembic migrations

## Development Commands
- Backend server: `cd backend; python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload`
- Frontend dev: `cd frontend; npm run dev`
- Database migration: `cd backend; python -m alembic upgrade head`
- Install backend deps: `cd backend; pip install -r requirements.txt`
- Install frontend deps: `cd frontend; npm install`

## File Paths
- Use Windows-style paths: `C:\Users\conta\source\repos\InsightVault`
- Use backslashes for Windows paths
- Current working directory: `C:\Users\conta\source\repos\InsightVault` 